&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;And here&amp;rsquo;s the raw output from that workflow run (I&amp;rsquo;ve truncated to just the job run):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;2022-07-14T01:27:14.0104402Z ##[group]Run echo &amp;#39;::add-mask::test&amp;#39;
2022-07-14T01:27:14.0104910Z [36;1mecho &amp;#39;::add-mask::test&amp;#39;[0m
2022-07-14T01:27:14.0105274Z [36;1mecho This is a test[0m
2022-07-14T01:27:14.0906476Z shell: /usr/bin/bash -e {0}
2022-07-14T01:27:14.0907141Z ##[endgroup]
2022-07-14T01:27:14.1473068Z This is a ***
2022-07-14T01:27:14.1729814Z Cleaning up orphan processes
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;Notice the second last line, where it says &lt;code&gt;This is a ***&lt;/code&gt;? that&amp;rsquo;s happened because we&amp;rsquo;ve used &lt;code&gt;add-mask&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;em&gt;mask&lt;/em&gt; ever time the work &lt;strong&gt;test&lt;/strong&gt; appears in our log, but you will see that it doesn&amp;rsquo;t mask it in the first 3 lines, because at that point, the mask &lt;em&gt;hasn&amp;rsquo;t&lt;/em&gt; yet been applied, so it doesn&amp;rsquo;t know to mask there (the first three lines are the logs dumping out the script that&amp;rsquo;s going to be run before it&amp;rsquo;s run).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That is a little bothersome, but realistically, you&amp;rsquo;re unlikely to have a hard-coded string in the workflow file that you want to mask in logs, after all, if it&amp;rsquo;s hard-coded in the workflow, then it&amp;rsquo;s already publicly visible, masking in logs won&amp;rsquo;t solve anything. Instead, you&amp;rsquo;re more likely to mask something that is computed, or retrieved from elsewhere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;masking-the-swa-deployment-token&#34;&gt;Masking the SWA deployment token &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34; href=&#34;#masking-the-swa-deployment-token&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=&#34;22px&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;22px&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s go back to the problem I originally had, I need to mask the deployment token I get from the Azure CLI.&lt;/p&gt;
